The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning approach for solving the Active Information Acquisition problem, which involves choosing a sequence of actions to acquire information about a process of interest using on-board sensors. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, with cs.AI being the most likely due to the focus on reinforcement learning.
